OL,6,FOf the total carbon stored, 98% can be
OL,7,Ffound in the top layer of the seabed
OL,8,Fsediments but it adds that some
OL,9,Fsediments are hundreds of metres
OL,10,Fthick, storing thousands of years'
OL,11,Fworth of carbon, so it is thought that
OL,12,Ftheir true storage is much greater.
OL,14,FThe remaining carbon is found in
OL,15,Fcoastal habitats such as saltmarshes
OL,16,Faround the coasts of England and Wales.
OL,18,FWhile these coastal regions only make
OL,19,Fup 1% of the UK seas, the report says
OL,20,Fareas "punch above their weight" as
OL,21,Fthey store 1.7% of the oceans carbon.
