OL,3,CLandmark report quantifies carbon in
OL,4,CUK seabeds
OL,6,FMarine protected areas (MPAs), which
OL,7,Fare already designated for nature
OL,8,Fprotection, store more than two-fifths
OL,9,Fof organic carbon, 105 million tonnes,
OL,10,Festimated to be in long-term storage
OL,11,Fin the seas.
OL,13,FCarbon is primarily absorbed by tiny
OL,14,Fplant-like organisms known as
OL,15,Fphytoplankton, which capture carbon
OL,16,Fdioxide through photosynthesis and
OL,17,Fdrift to the bottom of the sea when
OL,18,Fthey die, adding to the seabed
OL,19,Fsediment.
